The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.3 percent to 3,356.35.  Mirgor SACIFIA (MIRG AF), the Argentine builder of climate-
control systems for automobiles, advanced 2.1 percent to 123.50
pesos.  Argentina â€™s industrial production rose 8.2 percent in
June from a year earlier, the national statistics agency
reported in  Buenos Aires .  Sociedad Comercial del Plata SA (COME)  , a holding
company that produces and transports petroleum products and
natural gas through its subsidiaries, fell 1.3 percent to 0.775
pesos. Gas stations in Argentina face shortages and have been
unable to meet demand, resulting in long lines and limited
product options at the pump, and the problem is getting worse,
